EgyptAir has expanded its operations and increased flights into Kano, the commercial hub of Nigeria’s North-West. EgyptAir Country Manager, Muharram Abdel Rahman, announced that the company had upgraded its services to serve customers better, noting that it increased flight frequency to Kano from three to four times weekly. He said the new flight frequency took effect from April 14, 2022. He stated this during a news conference in Lagos recently. He said, “We are here today to announce our increase of frequencies into Kano as well as inform you of some upgrades we have done in the quality of our services to our customers. “Before now, EgyptAir used to operate three flights into Kano. But it is our pleasure to inform you that with effect from April 14, 2022, we have increased out frequency into Kano to four flights weekly on Sunday, Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday.” As a Star Alliance member, EgyptAir, the country manager disclosed, could connect its teeming customers to 120 destinations around the world, adding that the organisation had also upgraded its aircraft objectively to provide needed comfort as well. Rahman added, “We have also upgraded our aircraft on the route to an Airbus A330 which is equipped with onboard WiFi, personal charging ports, personal TV screens, and increased legroom for all our passengers in economy in a 2-4-2 configuration.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com